SUMMARY:LinkedIn Post 1: Introducing CEE FM [Company/Service]
DESCRIPTION:TOPIC: Introducing CEE FM\nTYPE: Company/Service\n\nIMAGE BRIEF: Wide-angle photo of a clean\, well-lit Budapest apartment building lobby or hotel reception area. Morning light. CEE FM logo watermark in corner.\n\n--- ENGLISH ---\nMost people never think about facility management. Until something breaks.\n\nCEE FM has spent 12 years making sure it does not.\n\nWe manage cleaning\, maintenance\, and operations for hotels\, apartment buildings\, and student housing in Budapest and across Hungary. Over 50 projects completed. A 9.5 client satisfaction rating.\n\nWe started in Budapest in 2012. Today we serve properties across Hungary.\n\nOur work is simple: keep buildings running. Keep tenants comfortable. Keep costs predictable.\n\nIf you manage a property in Budapest and want a partner who shows up on time and solves problems before they become emergencies\, let's talk.\n\noffice@ceefm.eu | +36 30 600 5400\n\n--- MAGYAR ---\nA legtobb ember nem gondol a letesitmenykezelesre. Amig valami el nem romlik.\n\nA CEE FM 12 eve azon dolgozik\, hogy ez ne tortenjen meg.\n\nTakaritast\, karbantartast es uzemeltetest vegzunk szallodak\, lakoepuletek es diakszallasok szamara Budapesten es egesz Magyarorszagon. Tobb mint 50 befejezett projekt. 9\,5-os ugyfel-elegedettsegi ertek.\n\n2012-ben Budapesten indultunk. Ma egesz Magyarorszagon szolgalunk ingatlanokat.\n\nA munkank egyszeru: az epuletek mukodjenek. A lakoknak legyen kenyelmes. A koltsegek legyenek kiszamithatoak.\n\nHa Budapesten ingatlant kezel es megbizhato partnert keres\, aki idoben erkezik es a problemakat meg azelott megoldja\, mielott surgosse valnak\, keressen minket.\n\noffice@ceefm.eu | +36 30 600 5400
STATUS:CONFIRMED
UID:ceefm-april-post01@bridgeworks.agency
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260402T070000Z
DTEND:20260402T073000Z
SUMMARY:LinkedIn Post 2: Spring Maintenance Checklist [Industry Insight]
DESCRIPTION:TOPIC: Spring maintenance checklist\nTYPE: Industry Insight\n\nIMAGE BRIEF: Flat-lay style graphic with maintenance icons: wrench\, thermometer\, checklist\, building outline. CEE FM brand colors.\n\n--- ENGLISH ---\nApril in Budapest means one thing for property managers: spring maintenance season.\n\nHere is what should be on your checklist right now:\n1. HVAC filter replacement. Winter buildup reduces efficiency by up to 25%.\n2. Roof and gutter inspection. Budapest's freeze-thaw cycles cause damage that shows up in spring.\n3. Window seal checks. Failing seals mean higher cooling costs all summer.\n4. Common area deep clean. Lobbies\, stairwells\, parking areas. Winter grime accumulates.\n5. Fire safety equipment testing. Extinguishers\, alarms\, emergency lighting. Compliance is not optional.\n6. Exterior facade review. Cracks from winter expansion need attention before they worsen.\n\nSkip any of these and you pay more later. Every time.\n\nWhat would you add to this list?\n\n--- MAGYAR ---\nAz aprilis Budapesten a letesitmenykezelok szamara egyet jelent: tavaszi karbantartasi szezon.\n\nEz most legyen a csekklistajan:\n\n1. Klimaberendezes szurocsereje. A teli lerakodas akar 25%-kal is csokkenti a hatekonysagot.\n2. Teto- es ereszcsatorna-ellenorzes. A budapesti fagyas-olvadas ciklusok tavaszra mutatjak meg a karokat.\n3. Ablaktomitesek ellenorzese. A hibas tomitesek egesz nyaron magasabb hutesi koltsegeket jelentenek.\n4. Kozos teruletek melytisztitasa. Aulak\, lepcsohazak\, parkolok. A teli szennyezodes felgyulemlik.\n5. Tuzvedelmi berendezesek tesztelese. Oltokeszulekek\, riasztok\, veszvilagitas. A megfeleles nem valasztas kerdese.\n6. Kulso homlokzat felulvizsgalata. A teli tagulasbol eredo repedeseket meg a rosszabbodas elott kell kezelni.\n\nHa ezek kozul barmit kihagy\, kesobb tobbet fizet. Minden alkalommal.\n\nMit tenne meg hozza a listahoz?
STATUS:CONFIRMED
UID:ceefm-april-post02@bridgeworks.agency
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260403T063000Z
DTEND:20260403T070000Z
SUMMARY:LinkedIn Post 3: What 5 AM Looks Like at a Budapest Hotel [Team/Culture]
DESCRIPTION:TOPIC: What 5 AM looks like at a Budapest hotel\nTYPE: Team/Culture\n\nIMAGE BRIEF: Black-and-white or muted-tone photo of a neatly made hotel bed. Early morning light through window.\n\n--- ENGLISH ---\n5:00 AM. The hotel lobby is quiet.\n\nOur team is already on-site.\n\nBy the time the first guest walks to breakfast\, three floors of rooms are already cleaned. Fresh linens. Restocked minibars. Bathrooms that pass a white-glove check.\n\nHotel housekeeping is not glamorous work. It is detailed work. It is invisible when done right. And guests notice immediately when it is not.\n\nOur housekeeping supervisors run shifts for properties across Budapest's city center. They manage schedules\, quality checks\, and supply chains for cleaning materials.\n\nThe best compliment we receive? "We did not even notice."\n\nThat is exactly the point.\n\n--- MAGYAR ---\nReggel 5:00. A szalloda aulaja csendes.\n\nA csapatunk mar a helyszinen van.\n\nMire az elso vendeg elindul reggelizni\, harom emelet szobai mar tisztak. Friss aggynemuk. Feltoltott minibarok. Feher kesztyu tesztet kiallo furdoszobak.\n\nA szallodai hazvezetoseg nem latvanyos munka. Reszletekre figyelo munka. Lathatatlan\, ha jol csinaljak. Es a vendegek azonnal eszreveszik\, ha nem.\n\nHazvezetosegi felugyeloink muszakokat iranyitanak Budapest belvarosaban. Beosztasokat\, minosegi ellenorzeseket es tisztitoszer-ellatasi lancokat kezelnek.\n\nA legjobb bok\, amit kapunk? "Eszre sem vettuk."\n\nPontosan ez a lenyeg.
STATUS:CONFIRMED
UID:ceefm-april-post03@bridgeworks.agency
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260408T070000Z
DTEND:20260408T073000Z
SUMMARY:LinkedIn Post 4: Eco-Friendly Cleaning Products [Company/Service]
DESCRIPTION:TOPIC: Eco-friendly cleaning products\nTYPE: Company/Service\n\nIMAGE BRIEF: Close-up of eco-friendly cleaning products with EU Ecolabel visible. Natural light. A gloved hand reaching for one of the bottles.\n\n--- ENGLISH ---\nWe stopped using conventional cleaning chemicals three years ago.\n\nNot because it was trendy. Because the numbers made sense.\n\nEco-friendly products cost 15-20% more per unit. But they reduce sick days among our cleaning staff by roughly a third. They eliminate chemical damage to surfaces\, which cuts replacement costs. And they satisfy the sustainability requirements that more hotel chains now demand from subcontractors.\n\nIn apartment buildings\, residents with allergies and small children notice the difference. Property managers get fewer complaints.\n\nOur cleaning team uses biodegradable\, EU Ecolabel-certified products across all Budapest properties. Same hygiene standards. Lower long-term cost. Safer for everyone in the building.\n\nGreen cleaning is not a marketing decision. It is an operations decision.\n\n--- MAGYAR ---\nHarom eve hagytuk abba a hagyomanyos tisztitoszerek hasznalatat.\n\nNem azert\, mert trendi volt. Azert\, mert a szamok igazoltak.\n\nA kornyezetbarat termekek darabonkent 15-20%-kal tobbe kerulnek. De a takarito szemelyzet tappenzet kozel egyharmadaval csokkentik. Megszuntetik a feluletek kemiai karosodasa\, ami csokkenti a cserekoltsegeket. Es teljesitik azokat a fenntarthatosagi kovetelmenyeket\, amelyeket egyre tobb szallodalanc elvar az alvallalkozoktol.\n\nLakoepuletekben az allergiasok es a kisgyermekes csaladok erzik a kulonbseget. Az ingatlankezelok kevesebb panaszt kapnak.\n\nTakarito csapatunk lebomlo\, EU okocimkes termekeket hasznal minden budapesti ingatlanon. Ugyanaz a higienes szinvonal. Alacsonyabb hosszu tavu koltseg. Biztonsagosabb mindenki szamara az epuletben.\n\nA zold takaritas nem marketingdontes. Uzemeltetesi dontes.
STATUS:CONFIRMED
UID:ceefm-april-post04@bridgeworks.agency
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260409T100000Z
DTEND:20260409T103000Z
SUMMARY:LinkedIn Post 5: Energy Costs and FM Solutions [Industry Insight]
DESCRIPTION:TOPIC: Energy costs and FM solutions\nTYPE: Industry Insight\n\nIMAGE BRIEF: Infographic-style visual showing energy cost reduction percentages. Navy and gold color scheme on ivory background.\n\n--- ENGLISH ---\nEnergy costs for Budapest commercial buildings rose 40% between 2022 and 2025.\n\nMost property managers absorbed the increase. Few optimized.\n\nHere is what we see working across our managed properties:\n\nLED lighting retrofits. Payback period: 8-14 months. After that\, pure savings.\nSmart HVAC scheduling. Matching heating and cooling to actual occupancy instead of fixed schedules cuts energy use by 15-20%.\nBuilding envelope audits. Finding and fixing air leaks is the cheapest energy upgrade available.\nMotion-sensor lighting in common areas. Lights that run 24/7 when nobody is there are burning money.\nRegular boiler and chiller maintenance. A 5% efficiency drop from neglected maintenance compounds fast across a full building.\n\nNone of this requires major capital investment. It requires attention.\n\n--- MAGYAR ---\nA budapesti kereskedelmi epuletek energiakoltsegei 2022 es 2025 kozott 40%-kal novekedtek.\n\nA legtobb ingatlankezelo elviselte a novekedest. Kevesen optimaltaltak.\n\nIme\, mit latunk mukodni a kezelt ingatlanainkon:\n\nLED vilagitas-atalakitas. Megterulesi ido: 8-14 honap. Utana tiszta megtakaritas.\nIntelligens HVAC utemiezes. A futes es hutes valos kihasznaltsaghoz igazitasa a fix utemezesek helyett 15-20%-kal csokkenti az energiafelhasznalast.\nEpuletburkolat-auditok. A legszivarglas felkutatasa es javitasa a legolcsobb elerheto energiakorszesites.\nMozgaserzekelos vilagitas kozos teruleteken. A 24 oraban ego lampak\, amikor senki sincs ott\, penzt egetnek.\nRendszeres kazan- es huto karbantartas. Az elhanyagolt karbantartasbol eredo 5%-os hatekonysagcsokkenes egy egesz epuletben gyorsan osszegzodik.\n\nEhhez nem kell nagy tokebefektetes. Odafigyeles kell.
STATUS:CONFIRMED
UID:ceefm-april-post05@bridgeworks.agency
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260410T070000Z
DTEND:20260410T073000Z
SUMMARY:LinkedIn Post 6: What Makes a Good Facility Supervisor [Team/Culture]
DESCRIPTION:TOPIC: What makes a good facility supervisor\nTYPE: Team/Culture\n\nIMAGE BRIEF: Portrait-style photo of a person in professional workwear standing in a building corridor. Real person\, not a model.\n\n--- ENGLISH ---\nWe have hired over 50 facility supervisors in 12 years.\n\nThe best ones share three traits:\n\nThey notice what others miss. A flickering light in a stairwell. A door that closes half a second slower than it should.\n\nThey communicate before problems escalate. A good supervisor calls you to say "the elevator is making a new sound\, I have scheduled the technician for Thursday" before you call them to say "the elevator is broken."\n\nThey respect the people on their team. Cleaning and maintenance staff work early hours\, physical shifts\, and often thankless roles. A supervisor who treats them well has lower turnover. Lower turnover means consistent quality.\n\nTechnical skills can be trained. These three traits cannot.\n\nIf this sounds like you\, we are hiring: office@ceefm.eu\n\n--- MAGYAR ---\n12 ev alatt tobb mint 50 letesitmenykezelesi felugyelot vettunk fel.\n\nA legjobbak harom kozos vonast mutatnak:\n\nEszreveszik\, amit masok nem. Egy villogo lampat a lepcsoahazban. Egy ajtot\, ami fel masodperccel lassabban csukodik\, mint kellene.\n\nKommunikalnak\, mielott a problemak sulyosbodnak. Egy jo felugyelo felhivja ont\, hogy "a lift uj hangot ad ki\, csutortokre beutemeztem a szerelot" mielott on hivna\, hogy "a lift elromlott."\n\nTisztelik a csapatuk tagjait. A takarito es karbantarto szemelyzet koran reggel dolgozik\, fizikailag megterhelo muszakokban es gyakran halatlan szerepekben. Az a felugyelo\, aki jol banik veluk\, alacsonyabb fluktuaciot er el. Az alacsonyabb fluktuacio kovetkezetes minoseget jelent.\n\nA technikai keszsegek tanithatoak. Ez a harom tulajdonsag nem.\n\nHa ez onre hasonlit\, keresunk munkatarsakat: office@ceefm.eu
STATUS:CONFIRMED
UID:ceefm-april-post06@bridgeworks.agency
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260415T070000Z
DTEND:20260415T073000Z
SUMMARY:LinkedIn Post 7: Hotel Housekeeping Standards Guests Notice [Industry Insight]
DESCRIPTION:TOPIC: Hotel housekeeping standards guests notice\nTYPE: Industry Insight\n\nIMAGE BRIEF: Split image: pristine hotel bathroom mirror reflection + perfectly made bed linens. Clean\, bright photography.\n\n--- ENGLISH ---\nHotel guests do not read your housekeeping SOP.\n\nBut they notice three things within 30 seconds of entering a room:\n\nThe bathroom. Specifically: the mirror\, the toilet rim\, and the drain. If any of those three are not spotless\, the entire room feels unclean.\n\nThe smell. Not air freshener. The absence of smell. A room should smell like nothing.\n\nThe bed. Wrinkle-free sheets and symmetrical pillows. Guests touch the bed first.\n\nEverything else matters too. But these three form the first impression. And first impressions drive reviews.\n\nAt CEE FM\, our quality inspections prioritize exactly these checkpoints. Because that is what your guests prioritize.\n\n--- MAGYAR ---\nA szallodavendegek nem olvassak el a hazvezetoseg muveleti eljarasait.\n\nDe harom dolgot harom masodpercen belul eszrevesznek a szobaba lepes utan:\n\nA furdoszobat. Pontosabban: a tukrot\, a WC-peremet es a lefolyot. Ha ezek kozul barmelyik nem makulatlan\, az egesz szoba tisztatalannak tunik.\n\nA szagot. Nem legfrissitot. A szag hianyat. Egy szobanak semmilyen szagunak nem kellene lennie.\n\nAz agyat. Rancmentes lepedok es szimmetrikus parnak. A vendegek eloszor az agyat erintik meg.\n\nMinden mas is szamit. De ez a harom alkotja az elso benyomast. Es az elso benyomas hatarozza meg az ertekelleseket.\n\nA CEE FM-nel a minosegi ellenorzseink pontosan ezeket az ellenorzo pontokat helyezik eloterbe. Mert a vendegei is ezt helyezik eloterbe.
STATUS:CONFIRMED
UID:ceefm-april-post07@bridgeworks.agency
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260416T070000Z
DTEND:20260416T073000Z
SUMMARY:LinkedIn Post 8: Student Housing FM Challenges [Company/Service]
DESCRIPTION:TOPIC: Student housing FM challenges\nTYPE: Company/Service\n\nIMAGE BRIEF: Photo of a modern student housing common area or study room. Clean\, functional design.\n\n--- ENGLISH ---\nStudent housing is not the same as hotel management. Property managers who treat it the same way lose money.\n\nHere is what is different:\n\nTurnover cycles are fixed. Move-in in September. Move-out in June. That two-week window is your entire deep maintenance window.\n\nDamage patterns are predictable. Kitchens and bathrooms take the most wear.\n\nCommunication must be direct and digital. Students do not read notice boards.\n\nCleaning frequency must be higher in common areas. These spaces serve 50-200 people daily.\n\nCEE FM manages student housing facilities in Budapest and across Hungary. We know the cycle. We plan around it.\n\n--- MAGYAR ---\nA diakszallas nem ugyanaz\, mint a szallodakezeles. Azok az ingatlankezelok\, akik ugyanugy kezelik\, penzt veszitenek.\n\nIme\, mi mas:\n\nA forgasi ciklusok rogzitettek. Bekoltozes szeptemberben. Kikoltozes juniusban. A ket tanev kozti ket hetes idoszak az egyetlen melyitett karbantartasi ablak.\n\nA karosodasok kiszamithatoak. A konyhak es furdoszobak kopnak a legjobban.\n\nA kommunikacionak kozvetlennek es digitalisnak kell lennie. A diakok nem olvasnak hirdetotablat.\n\nA takaritasi gyakoriksagnak magasabbnak kell lennie a kozos teruleteken. Ezek a terek naponta 50-200 embert szolgalnak ki.\n\nA CEE FM diakszallasokat kezel Budapesten es egesz Magyarorszagon. Ismerjuk a ciklust. Tervezunk kore.
STATUS:CONFIRMED
UID:ceefm-april-post08@bridgeworks.agency
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260417T100000Z
DTEND:20260417T103000Z
SUMMARY:LinkedIn Post 9: Smart Building Tech ROI [Industry Insight]
DESCRIPTION:TOPIC: Smart building tech ROI\nTYPE: Industry Insight\n\nIMAGE BRIEF: Clean tech-forward graphic. Icons: thermostat\, water sensor\, mobile ticket\, lightbulb with wifi. Each paired with ROI number. Navy/gold/ivory.\n\n--- ENGLISH ---\nEvery facility management conference in 2026 talks about smart buildings.\n\nMost of the technology being sold has a payback period longer than the contract term. Here is what actually works:\n\nSmart thermostats with occupancy sensing. Cost: 200-400 EUR. Savings: 10-18%. Payback: under 2 years.\n\nWater leak sensors. Cost: 50-100 EUR. A single undetected leak can cause 10\,000+ EUR in damage.\n\nDigital maintenance ticketing. Cost: 30-80 EUR/month. Benefit: traceable response times\, accountability.\n\nIoT-connected lighting. Cost: moderate. Payback: 3-4 years.\n\nDigital twins and AI predictive maintenance? Promising for large portfolios. Overkill for a 50-unit building.\n\nStart with what pays back fastest. Scale from there.\n\n--- MAGYAR ---\nMinden 2026-os letesitmenykezelesi konferencia az okos epuletekrol beszel.\n\nAz eladott technologia nagy reszenek megterulesi ideje hosszabb\, mint a szerzodes idotartama. Ime\, mi mukodik valoban:\n\nOkos termosztatok jelenleterzekelelessel. Koltseg: 200-400 EUR darabonkent. Megtakaritas: 10-18% futesre es hutesre. Megterules: 2 even belul.\n\nVizszivargas-erzekeleok. Koltseg: 50-100 EUR erzekelonkent. Egyetlen eszre nem vett szivargas 10 000+ EUR kart okozhat.\n\nDigitalis karbantartasi jegykezelo. Koltseg: havi 30-80 EUR ingatlanonkent. Elony: nyomon kovetheto valaszidok\, elszamoltathatosag.\n\nIoT-kapcsolt vilagitas kozos teruleteken. Koltseg: mersekelt. Megterules: 3-4 ev.\n\nDigitalis ikrek es MI-vezerelt prediktiv karbantartas? Igeretes nagy portfoliokhoz. Tulzas egy 50 lakasos epulethez.\n\nKezdje azzal\, ami a leggyorsabban terul meg. Onnan skalazzon.
STATUS:CONFIRMED
UID:ceefm-april-post09@bridgeworks.agency
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260422T070000Z
DTEND:20260422T073000Z
SUMMARY:LinkedIn Post 10: Sustainability in Practice - Earth Day [Company/Service]
DESCRIPTION:TOPIC: Sustainability in practice (Earth Day)\nTYPE: Company/Service\n\nIMAGE BRIEF: Photo: eco cleaning products in use\, waste sorting station\, or maintenance worker repairing equipment.\n\n--- ENGLISH ---\n"Sustainability" is the most overused word in facility management marketing.\n\nHere is what it means in our daily operations:\n\nWe use EU Ecolabel-certified cleaning products at every property. No exceptions.\n\nWe sort and track waste volumes monthly across all managed buildings.\n\nWe run quarterly energy audits for properties under long-term contracts.\n\nOur maintenance schedules prioritize repair over replacement. A reconditioned door closer lasts another 5 years.\n\nWe train every team member on resource efficiency in their first week. Practical\, on-site training.\n\nWe are not perfect. No FM company is. But we measure\, report\, and improve. Every quarter.\n\n--- MAGYAR ---\nA "fenntarthatosag" a leginkabb tulhasznalt szo a letesitmenykezelesi marketingben.\n\nIme\, mit jelent a napi muveleteinkben:\n\nEU okocimkes tisztitoszereket hasznalunk minden ingatlanon. Kivetel nelkul.\n\nHavonta valogatjuk es kovetjuk a hulladekmennyisegeket az osszes kezelt epuletben.\n\nNegyedevente energiaauditot vegzunk a hosszu tavu szerzodes alatt allo ingatlaloknal.\n\nKarbantartasi utemterveink a javitast reszesitik elonyben a cserevel szemben. Egy felujitott ajtocsuoko meg 5 evig kibir.\n\nMinden csapattagot az elso heten kepzunk az eroforras-hatekonysag teren. Gyakorlati\, helyszini kepzes.\n\nNem vagyunk tokeletesek. Egyetlen FM ceg sem az. De merunk\, jelentunk es fejlodunk. Minden negyedevben.
STATUS:CONFIRMED
UID:ceefm-april-post10@bridgeworks.agency
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260423T070000Z
DTEND:20260423T073000Z
SUMMARY:LinkedIn Post 11: Budapest Property Boom and FM [Industry Insight]
DESCRIPTION:TOPIC: Budapest property boom and FM\nTYPE: Industry Insight\n\nIMAGE BRIEF: Aerial or elevated photo of Budapest skyline with modern buildings. Or a simple map of Budapest districts with growth indicators.\n\n--- ENGLISH ---\nBudapest's office market is 4.25 million square meters. Second largest in Central Europe after Warsaw.\n\nThe hotel sector added 1\,200+ new rooms in 2025 alone. Student housing developments are expanding across Districts 8\, 9\, and 13.\n\nMore buildings means more demand for facility management. But not just any facility management.\n\nProperty owners are shifting from "find the cheapest cleaning company" to "find a partner who manages everything under one contract." Integrated FM contracts are growing at nearly 7% annually in the CEE region.\n\nWhat is driving this? Complexity.\n\nIf you manage property in Budapest\, the question is no longer whether you need professional facility management. It is whether your current provider can keep up.\n\n--- MAGYAR ---\nBudapest irodapiaca 4\,25 millio negyzetmeter. Kozep-Europa masodik legnagyobb piaca Varso utan.\n\nA szallodai szektor egyedul 2025-ben tobb mint 1200 uj szobaval bovult. A diakszallas-fejlesztesek a 8.\, 9. es 13. keruletben bovulnek.\n\nTobb epulet tobb letesitmenykezelesi igenyt jelent. De nem akarmilyen letesitmenykezelest.\n\nAz ingatlantulajdonosok a "keressuk a legolcsobb takarito ceget" megkozelitestol a "keressunk egy partnert\, aki mindent egy szerzodes alatt kezel" fele mozognak. Az integralt FM szerzodesek evente kozel 7%-kal nonek a KKE regioban.\n\nMi hajtja ezt? Az osszetetteseg.\n\nHa Budapesten ingatlant kezel\, a kerdes mar nem az\, hogy szuksege van-e professzionalis letesitmenykezelesre. Hanem az\, hogy a jelenlegi szolgaltatoja kepes-e lepest tartani.
STATUS:CONFIRMED
UID:ceefm-april-post11@bridgeworks.agency
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260424T070000Z
DTEND:20260424T073000Z
SUMMARY:LinkedIn Post 12: Five Reasons to Outsource FM [Company/Service]
DESCRIPTION:TOPIC: Five reasons to outsource FM\nTYPE: Company/Service\n\nIMAGE BRIEF: Clean comparison graphic: left side 'In-house' with complexity icons\, right side 'CEE FM' with unified interface. Navy and gold on ivory.\n\n--- ENGLISH ---\nYou can manage your building's facilities in-house. Many property owners do.\n\nHere are five reasons they eventually stop:\n\n1. Staff coverage. A sick day creates an immediate service gap. An FM company has backup staff within hours.\n2. Procurement costs. We buy at volume pricing. A single building cannot match those rates.\n3. Compliance tracking. An FM company tracks fire safety\, hygiene certs\, and servicing records automatically.\n4. Scalability. Adding a second property means expanding a contract\, not doubling your team.\n5. Focus. Managing cleaners\, electricians\, plumbers\, and security is a full-time job.\n\nOutsourcing is not about cutting corners. It is about putting each task in the hands of people who do it every day.\n\nCEE FM has been that partner for 50+ properties. Reach out: office@ceefm.eu\n\n--- MAGYAR ---\nKezelhetik az epuletuk letesitmenyeit hazon belul. Sok ingatlantulajdonos igy tesz.\n\nIme ot ok\, amiert vegul abbahagyjak:\n\n1. Szemelyzeti lefedettseg. Egy betegszabadsag azonnali szolgaltatasi rest teremt. Egy FM ceg orakon belul rendelkezik potszemellettel.\n2. Beszerzesi koltsegek. Mi tisztitoszereket\, karbantartasi alkatreszeket es felszerelest nagybani aron vasarlunk.\n3. Megfelelosegi nyomon kovetes. Tuzvedelmi ellenorzesek\, higieniai tanusitvanyok\, berendezes-szervielesi nyilvantartasok. Egy FM ceg automatikusan koveti ezeket.\n4. Skalazhatosag. Egy masodik ingatlan hozzaadasa egy szerzodes boviteset jelenti.\n5. Fokusz. Takaritok\, villanyszerelok\, vizvezetekk-szerelok es biztonsagi orok kezelese teljes allasu munka.\n\nA kiszervezes nem a sarkok levagasarol szol. Arrol\, hogy minden feladatot olyan emberek kezebe adunk\, akik minden nap ezt csinaljak.\n\nA CEE FM tobb mint 50 ingatlannak volt ilyen partnere. Keressen minket: office@ceefm.eu
STATUS:CONFIRMED
UID:ceefm-april-post12@bridgeworks.agency
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR